---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout title="Law Firm | PoliceConduct.org" pagePath="/partner/law-firm/">
  <main class="flex-grow-1">
    <section class="py-vh-3 bg-gray-100 border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <ol class="breadcrumb mb-3">
            <li class="breadcrumb-item">
              <a class="link-dark" href="/partner/">Partners</a>
            </li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">Law Firm</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-end">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
            <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-2">
              Value proposition
            </p>
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">From Evidence to Impact</h1>
            <p class="lead text-muted mb-0">
              Strategic infrastructure for civil rights and criminal defense
              litigation.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">Built for</div>
                <div class="fw-semibold">
                  Civil rights and criminal defense firms
                </div>
                <div class="text-muted small">
                  Structured data turns individual incidents into systemic
                  claims.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold">1. Building the Monell claim</h2>
            <p class="text-muted">
              Establishing municipal liability requires proving a custom or
              policy of misconduct. That is nearly impossible with a single case
              file.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
              <li>
                Pattern-of-conduct analytics to link similar reports across a
                department.
              </li>
              <li>
                Department heat maps that show recurring misconduct hotspots.
              </li>
              <li>
                Evidence to prove deliberate indifference by city leadership.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">
                  Civil rights pitch
                </div>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  We provide the evidentiary foundation to pierce municipal
                  immunity and build a Monell-ready record under Section 1983.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-light border-top border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">
          2. Courtroom-ready evidence preservation
        </h2>
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  Immediate statement capture
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Contemporaneous records</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Give clients a safe, independent link to record the arrest
                  timeline while details are fresh.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-6">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  Evidence vaulting
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Chain of custody</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Link raw video, witness statements, and photos to a structured
                  case file so public-interest evidence stays intact.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">3. Strategic redaction workflow</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Control how and when evidence is published while protecting witness
          identities and litigation strategy.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Private drafts</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Create and store reports privately for internal firm use.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Controlled publication</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Release evidence or summaries only when it supports case
                  strategy.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Anonymized reporting</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Protect client identities while still contributing to pattern
                  data.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-gray-100 border-top border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">4. Partnership value proposition</h2>
        <div class="table-responsive">
          <table class="table table-bordered align-middle">
            <thead class="table-light">
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">Feature</th>
                <th scope="col">For civil rights firms</th>
                <th scope="col">For criminal defense firms</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Monell data aggregation</strong></td>
                <td>Links cases to prove policy or custom.</td>
                <td>Identifies credibility and impeachment patterns.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Case file short-links</strong></td>
                <td>Drive public awareness and witness recruitment.</td>
                <td>Provide structured timelines for defense teams.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Pattern alerts</strong></td>
                <td>Notify you when new reports hit active defendants.</td>
                <td>Flags officers with recurring Brady/Giglio issues.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Redaction tools</strong></td>
                <td>Protect sensitive litigation strategy.</td>
                <td>Ensure 2026-compliant client privacy.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-start">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  Partner resource kit
                </p>
                <h2 class="h5 fw-semibold mb-0">Tools for law firms</h2>
                <p class="text-muted mb-0">
                  Assets that standardize intake and amplify evidence strategy.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
            <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-3">
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold mb-1">Pre-litigation intake form</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  A standardized template for clients immediately after a police
                  interaction.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold mb-1">Verified attorney seal</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  A badge for your website signaling commitment to data-driven
                  accountability.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold mb-1">
                  Case notification subscription
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Alerts when a new report is filed against an officer tied to
                  your active cases.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div
          class="d-flex flex-column flex-lg-row align-items-lg-center justify-content-between gap-3"
        >
          <div>
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-1">Ready to build stronger cases?</h2>
            <p class="text-muted mb-0">
              We can draft a Notice of Claim template that cites
              PoliceConduct.org data.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a
            class="btn btn-dark rounded-0"
            href="/about/contact?whoami=Partner&message=I%27m%20interested%20in%20a%20law%20firm%20Notice%20of%20Claim%20template%20using%20PoliceConduct.org%20data."
          >
            Request the Notice of Claim template
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
